/*!
  \page tools_overview PandA Tools and Libraries
 
  \section src_intro Introduction
  The PandA project contains the the set of tools and libraries reported below.


  \section src_tools Tools
  The tools that can be configured and so enabled are:
    - \ref bambu_overview provides high-level synthesis functionalities
    - \ref eucalyptus_overview allows the characterization of resources in the technology library


  \section src_subprojects Libraries sub-projects 
  Creation and management of internal intermediate representations:
  - Parser components provide the front-end readers used to acquire the inputs consumed by the analysis and synthesis flows.
  - Graph components define the graph-based program and design descriptions used throughout the framework.
  - POLIXML components provide the lightweight XML infrastructure used by configuration and exchange formats.
  - Subproject \ref src_behavior_page "Behavior:" contains functions to manage and to represent graphs with different granularity. In particular we can represent CFG/DFG/CDG/DDG/SDG for operations and CFG/DFG/Dom/PostDom for basic blocks.
  - IR components provide the data structures used to represent the PandA internal intermediate representation.
  - Frontend analysis components build and transform the PandA internal intermediate representation.
  - Backend components emit C, SystemC, VHDL, and Verilog descriptions.

  Resource library and circuit representation management:
  - Technology components manage libraries, device data, and technology-specific information.
  - Subproject \ref src_circuit_page "Circuit:" describes a generic data structure representing a circuit.
  - Wrapper components provide adapters around external compilation and synthesis tools.

  Bambu tool:
  - Subproject \ref src_HLS_page provides algorithms for high-level synthesis.

  Development aids: 
  - Utility algorithms provide reusable building blocks for analyses, transformations, and internal services.
  - Utility components contain common helpers, macros, and support infrastructure.


*/
